nalysis so seamlessly that art and life become extensions of each other, Shapiro embodies in his lively prose the very qualities he celebrates in the poems he loves. Brimming with wit and insight, this is a book for poets, students and scholars of poetry, teachers of literature, and everyone who cares about the literary arts and how they illuminate our personal and public lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPoetry. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aessay collection, essays, anthology, collected, memoir, biography, autobiography, autobiographical, biographical, literary, criticism, critique, analysis, fusion, interdisciplinary, genre, life, true story, poetry, poet, poetic, poetics, humor, teacher, conventions, norms, taboo, literature, self expression, art, artistic, scholarly, academic, personal, public, mark twain, translation, linguistic.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226417004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226417004/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles